This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) because it presents a self-training approach to unsupervised dependency parsing. It also uses supervised parsing algorithms, which could potentially place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of probability models could suggest a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
